The paper discusses neural network models for autoassociative, distributed memory, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses generalization properties, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses similarity search, which is a topic in information retrieval and databases, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Information Retrieval) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of these techniques, which is a topic in information theory and optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category as well.
